S'text/html'
p230
sg36
Nsg37
VEver since I finally started to wear men's clothes more and more, I have cared about my appearance more in a proportional amount. Actually, it might also be because I am seriously attracted to someone for the first time as well. I have no idea. Before I wanted to look masculine, but that was it. At first it was just hygiene. I was sure to brush my teeth well, wash my hair, put on deoderant, and apply chap stick. This was good as sometimes I had minor issues with that before. This is not an uncommon issue for people on the autism spectrum.<br /><br />Now I find myself not just focusing on hygiene but on other things. I am trying to lose weight and doing okay. I do not let my clothes get too dirty. Most of all, I keep wondering what makes a person likeable and attractive. <br /><br />I think I am fairly likeable as a friend and have a decent personality. Please correct me if I am wrong. But this attraction business is new to me. Sometimes I wonder if I will ever be liked as a male. Physically I seem to have little chance and even losing weight and staying clean will only help a little. However, I have observed that much of attraction seems to be personality based.<br /><br />I do not want to change my personality. I would like to minimise its flaws. The issue is that I do not know very much about my personality and no one I have asked can seem to pinpoint it. I wish I could break this into clear-cut segments, but it does not work that way.<br /><br />Some people say that I have a good personality, but as far as I know, no one has been attracted to me. Maybe I am not cut out for that sort of thing. Do I lack a sense of humor? A good smile? Am I too awkward? What am I doing wrong?<br /><br />Drat it, I dislike whining but this sort of thing is confusing and nearly hopeless for someone who is autistic and transgendered. People keep saying that someone will love me sometime but somehow I doubt it as the days pass.<br /><br />I hate myself for thinking this way. It makes me seem like a shallow person, even to myself. I have never been like this before.<div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width="1" height="1" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/1848101302710400415-4065518719065746154?l=shadowmechanic.blogspot.com" alt="" /></div>
