VI thought about not posting poetry because over the past years the idea that unmetered poetry is bad has been forced upon me. If people have complaints, tell me and I will stop.<br /><br />People also say not to insert the author's life into poetry in analysis. In this case, my life is crucial to understanding the true meaning.<br /><br />Shadows glistening on the ice,<br />flakes enveloping the grass,<br />winter arrives tonight,<br />the snow returns at last.<br /><br />People shiver in dread,<br />children cry out with glee,<br />the coming cold marches steadily on<br />into a freezing eternity.<br /><br />A light glistens in the distance, <br />faintly and precariously.<br />Although the cutting chills endure,<br />perhaps people can sustain <br />with that little light in mind.<br /><br />Eternity is not infinite,<br />time thaws away<br />and with it the water runs,<br />ushering in a bright spring day.<div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width="1" height="1" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/1848101302710400415-1280306301470596629?l=shadowmechanic.blogspot.com" alt="" /></div>
