Nsg37
VThe shadows make me comfortable. As a young child, I watched my shadow change and morph with great fascination. Most people see shadows as a warped reflection of reality. Not so for me. Shadows were clearer than reality. Not so anymore. Yet, I still lurk here in the darkness.<br /><br />I am transgendered, gay, and autistic. Those  will be my primary topics although some academic and philosophical  topics might come up in the process.&nbsp; <br /><br />This blog will be a mix of journal entries, essays, and stories about my past. I might also post some news articles, commentaries, and reviews. Do not expect it to be highly polished. However, I will post often and write fairly well.<br /><br />Please read whatever interests you. I will tag posts so that people can read only certain parts of this if they wish. However, I encourage you to read it all.<div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width="1" height="1" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/1848101302710400415-12571780613745147?l=shadowmechanic.blogspot.com" alt="" /></div>
